28/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski is in Belgrade on Monday (28 February) for talks with Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic, Serbian President Boris Tadic and Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica. Prior to the visit, Buckovski told reporters that economic co-operation and foreign investments are crucial to the region. He stressed, however, that regional development is impossible without sustained security, which he linked to the Kosovo issue.
In other news, some employees of the state-run Macedonian Railways began a hunger strike Monday to protest government measures to restructure the ailing company. On Friday, other workers walked off their jobs, blocking rail traffic throughout the country. (Macedonian government Web site, A1 TV - 28/02/05; Beta, Tanjug, Makfax - 27/02/05)
